// -- NEW DISCUSSION -- //

==>TOPIC: WEB SERVICES WITH SOAP

From: Rajesh Chawla <rc@trcs.com>

Hi folks,

I'm getting more and more into SOAP. It provides me with the ability
to expose proprietary code in a relatively painless fashion using an
XML standard that has the potential of working through a firewall.

I'm very curious to hear if other folks are using SOAP or am I out
on a limb again :-)

Regards,
Rajesh

[ Moderator Comment ]

SOAP stands for Simple Object Access Protocol and relates to the
passing of messages between web service applications (remote
procedure calls).  It seems that SOAP is the dominant message
protocol to emerge from several alternatives as it has been adopted
by industry in the form of a W3C recommendation.

A good reference for reading about SOAP is the W3C's Primer:
http://www.w3.org/TR/2002/CR-soap12-part0-20021219/

~ Pete

Comment? mailto:develop@adventive.com

